{"title": "The sleep deprivation and burnout of new parenthood", "tags": "opinion", "timestamp": "2024-05-30", "content": "I can\u2019t say I hadn\u2019t been forewarned. As soon as I got pregnant, other mummy friends charged me to sleep as much as I could because I would never sleep the same way again.\nI took this cryptic advice as casually as it was given. Like most working Singaporeans, I was no stranger to late nights. I started my career in a publishing house where writers frequently worked past 10pm to meet a deadline. All this and more, I was willing to endure for an offspring. How bad could it be?"}